TAGALOG

Sa Filipino, walang mga salitang "parin," "narin," "palang," "nalang," o "nanaman."
Bukod na salita ang mga pang-angkop o ligature na "na" at "pa."

* Pa rin - still, nevertheless
* Na rin - also, finally
* Pa lang - so far
* Na lang - just
* Na naman - again




******************************

ENGLISH











PSA: There are no words like these in the Filipino language. If you really care about proper grammar, you should have at least show some effort to put a space between “pa” and “na” and the words that you often attach to it. Everyone needs space. (luh)

Wrong to correct usage:

parin = Mahal pa rin kita.
narin = Hindi na rin siguro.
palang = Nandito pa lang ako sa MRT.
nalang = ‘Wag na lang, pagod na ako.
nanaman = Nandito ka na naman?
